        "creation_date": 1513846374,
        "body": "<p>Yes and no. A noted <a href=\"http://www.jfree.org/forum/viewtopic.php?f=3&amp;t=119664\" rel=\"noreferrer\">here<\/a> in 1.5.0, <code>createBarChart3D<\/code> is gone but <code>createBarChart<\/code> has been improved. So you either stay on 1.0.19 and use <code>createBarChart3D<\/code>, or upgrade to 1.5.0 and use <code>createBarChart<\/code> (or use another framework for your graphs).<\/p>\n\n<p>1.5.0's <code>createBarChart<\/code> has a Mario-Brothers-pipe-3D-effect that (in my opinion) make it look better than 1.0.19's 3D charts. So my recommendation is to go for 1.5.0's <code>createBarChart<\/code>.<\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 47921267,
